    "summary": "The community centers around JUMP, BEQ, and BRANCH instructions, along with the EX/MEM寄存器. These entities are interconnected through their roles in controlling program flow and data transfer within a processor. JUMP and BEQ are related through their control signals, while BRANCH and BEQ interact in conditional branching. The EX/MEM寄存器 plays a role in transmitting branch target addresses to the program counter. The community's structure reflects the technical aspects of processor architecture, particularly in instruction execution and control mechanisms.",
