            "explanation": "The '操作系统内核' (operating system kernel) is responsible for managing the creation, scheduling, and termination of processes. It provides the foundational mechanisms that enable processes to run concurrently and communicate with each other. This role is critical for system stability and performance, as any issues within the kernel could lead to widespread system failures. [Data: Relationships (916)]"
        },
        {
