        },
        {
            "summary": "Buffer management and its risks",
            "explanation": "Buffers are used to temporarily store data during inter-process communication and I/O operations. While they improve efficiency, buffers can become a source of deadlocks if not managed correctly. The relationship between buffers and processes highlights the need for careful resource allocation and synchronization to prevent such issues. [Data: Relationships (1086)]"
