            "explanation": "The First-Come-First-Served (FCFS) scheduling algorithm significantly affects both waiting time and turnaround time. According to the data, FCFS leads to increased waiting time because it does not preempt the processor [Data: Relationships (1037)]. This non-preemptive nature means that once a process starts executing, it runs to completion before the next process is handled, potentially causing longer waits for subsequent processes. Additionally, FCFS impacts turnaround time, as the order in which processes are executed directly influences their total execution time [Data: Relationships (1033)]. This can result in longer overall processing times for processes that arrive later, even if they require less CPU time. The relationship between FCFS and these metrics is crucial in understanding the algorithm's limitations and its implications for system efficiency. [Data: Relationships (1037, 1033, 1036, 1042)]"
